narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: weekly assignments force students to engage with material without being too overwhelming; selection of readings provides a good balance for all prior knowledge levels; guest lecturers were all fantastic and very insightful. Weaknesses: course suffers from being a bit too broad, such that it is hard to go in-depth to any single topic; discussion parts of the class were dysfunctional and unhelpful due to the size of the class, and quickly became students just spouting their single points without interacting with other points made.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes if someone wanted a general overview of some topics in global finance to explore and later dive into. No if the student was looking for a course to gain specific skills or subject expertise.
